      {
        "id": 3266481,
        "name": "Chris_Rickey",
        "username": "crickey",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/c/fbc32d/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2021-11-04T13:46:07.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Thank you for your response William. My comment on attention to tasting notes goes for your notes as well. It\u2019s just that you have a larger database of champagne notes I can access so I\u2019m starting to get a better handle on your descriptions. I know Alan is an experienced champagne aficionado, but I don\u2019t have a good sense how his notes translate. Perhaps the difference, as you suggest, is simply due to Alan\u2019s bottle being young and never having unwound as he drank it.</p>",
