        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2021-11-04T18:21:34.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"6\" data-topic=\"174535\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>I haven\u2019t tried this bottling yet, but the Doyard Blanc des Blancs \u201cRevolution\u201d turned my head.  I immediately went back for more of all of their wines offered in my market.  I found the Revolution very generous and fruit-forward for a non-dose wine.  I typically find that non-dose misses something for my palate, just as much as too high a dosage leads to a wine seeming to be overdone.  It\u2019s a goldilocks problem for me.  This one was complete as delivered and I was smitten.  As to fruit profile\u2026orchard fruit (pear and apple), hazelnut and almond with maybe a citrus note accenting things.  Lovely and reasonably priced for what it is.</p>\n<p>Cheers,<br>\nfred</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>They are very serious at every step of the process!</p>",
