      {
        "id": 3266965,
        "name": "alan weinberg",
        "username": "alan_weinberg",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/alan_weinberg/{size}/647_2.png",
        "created_at": "2021-11-05T02:42:39.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"5\" data-topic=\"174535\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Thank you for your response William. My comment on attention to tasting notes goes for your notes as well. It\u2019s just that you have a larger database of champagne notes I can access so I\u2019m starting to get a better handle on your descriptions. I know Alan is an experienced champagne aficionado, but I don\u2019t have a good sense how his notes translate. Perhaps the difference, as you suggest, is simply due to Alan\u2019s bottle being young and never having unwound as he drank it.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I\u2019d listen to William\u2014I did and bought the wine. It\u2019s probably, at 7 years old, one of the youngest I\u2019ve ever tasted. At William\u2019s tender young age, his experience already dwarfs mine. I believe his note, but I also described how I found it. Maybe I drank it too cold.  Definitely drank it too young.</p>",
